    "In particular, we tread in the domain of generalization and its interplay with the ability to memorize random data.",
    "The main idea of our work builds on the theory of randomization tests from non-parametric statistics 63.",
    "Figure 1 contains a visualization of our framework.Initially, we train QNNs on quantum states whose labels have been randomized and compare the training accuracy achieved by the same learning model when trained on the true labels.",
    "Our results reveal that, in many cases, the models learn to classify the training data perfectly, regardless of whether the labels have been randomized.",
    "By altering the input data, we reach our first finding: Observation 1."
